Deutsche Bank’s Ackermann May Replace Boersig, Handelsblatt Says

-- B y   H o l g e r   E l f e s
-- 
2011-07-01T16:59:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-01/deutsche-bank-s-ackermann-may-replace-boersig-handelsblatt-says.html
Deutsche Bank AG (DBK) ’s Chief Executive
Officer  Josef Ackermann  is willing to move to the lender’s
supervisory board, replacing the current chairman, Clemens Boersig, the newspaper  Handelsblatt  reported today, citing
unidentified people familiar with the matter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Holger Elfes in Dusseldorf at 
 helfes@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at   cperri@bloomberg.net . 